1
00:00:20,037 --> 00:00:23,360
King Nanda Bayin will lead the campaign against King Thado Minsaw of Inwa

2
00:00:23,617 --> 00:00:25,520
You started this war yourself.

3
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:28,480
An uncle and nephew fighting for power. I will not waste our strength.

4
00:00:28,517 --> 00:00:31,560
I sent a message to Prince Nares, inviting him to come and negotiate.

5
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:34,000
Mangjaparo instead ordered men to lie in wait and attack,

6
00:00:34,203 --> 00:00:36,760
At this moment, I am deemed guilty

7
00:00:36,923 --> 00:00:38,124
of treachery and rebellion.

8
00:00:38,397 --> 00:00:40,398
And the death penalty is unavoidable.

9
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:43,920
As the King of Hongsawadi has not acted in good faith

10
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:47,880
I hereby declare the cities of Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya

11
00:00:48,097 --> 00:00:50,800
and the city of Hongsawadi to be severed,

12
00:00:51,143 --> 00:00:53,044
That the Hongsawadi army has just triumphed over Inwa.

13
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:56,045
If he learns of your rebellion, you will certainly face a heavy onslaught.

14
00:00:56,430 --> 00:00:59,240
I would like to make a request take my sister back to Ayutthaya.

15
00:00:59,503 --> 00:01:00,800
This matter is a secret.

16
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,920
It cannot be done with such fanfare that others find out.

17
00:01:03,483 --> 00:01:04,960
Why have you come alone?

18
00:01:05,317 --> 00:01:06,320
I have come to bid farewell.

19
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,440
But I cannot leave my child and my attendants behind.

20
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:29,800
I dispatched my army from Hongsawadi.

21
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:35,560
I also led the rest of Ayutthaya people to go back with me.

22
00:02:10,883 --> 00:02:12,800
We were marching through Martaban.

23
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:17,040
Phra Maha Thera pursuaded Mon people to follow me.

24
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,960
Phraya Kian and Phraya Ram also tagged along.

25
00:02:37,263 --> 00:02:39,000
May you find peace, Prince Nares.

26
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:41,043
Are you exhausted, Sir?

27
00:02:41,697 --> 00:02:42,720
Your Highness, we are in big trouble.

28
00:02:43,790 --> 00:02:44,791
What is the matter?

29
00:02:44,997 --> 00:02:46,700
Hongsawadi army is following us.

30
00:02:47,210 --> 00:02:49,050
They will reach us in two days.

31
00:02:50,743 --> 00:02:52,500
Hongsawadi army just left Inwa.

32
00:02:53,370 --> 00:02:54,500
Why did they reach us here so fast?

33
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:58,600
They're the small troop, led by Phraya Chanto.

34
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:01,360
They figured out our plan so they sent the small troop first.

35
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:03,160
What is your plan, Your Highness?

36
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:11,720
There are children, women and elderly joining us.

37
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:13,441
We can't walk that fast.

38
00:03:14,310 --> 00:03:17,360
We won't make it if we tried to run away from them.

39
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:24,960
If we can't run away from them, then it's fight time, Sir.

40
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,840
We are outnumbered. If we can't fight against them,

41
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,880
I'm worried that our people will die.

42
00:03:44,443 --> 00:03:46,880
Sir, can you lead our people to march back?

43
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,960
Duang, you need to lead troop no.1 to guard them back.

44
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:54,761
Phet and Sri, you need to gather our elite soldiers here.

45
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:58,400
We will come back to fight with Hongsawadi army and stop them.

46
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,681
Yes, Your Highness.

47
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:09,440
Everyone, you need to pack up and ready to leave.

48
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:12,520
Come on. Hurry up! We need to go.

49
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,400
Thado Minsaw of Inwa lost the battle

50
00:05:40,717 --> 00:05:41,960
so he escaped the city.

51
00:05:42,970 --> 00:05:45,880
I will appoint Min Letya to rule the city instead.

52
00:05:46,543 --> 00:05:49,920
He will take care of Inwa, be my eyes and my ears.

53
00:05:51,037 --> 00:05:52,480
As you command, Your Majesty.

54
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:55,360
Any updates on Phraya Chanto's side?

55
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:59,280
He led 50,000 members of infantry

56
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,040
to attack Prince Nares' troops,

57
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:04,400
they reached Sittoung River but there is no announcement of any victory.

58
00:06:07,463 --> 00:06:10,680
In fact, this battle shouldn't have happened.

59
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:17,640
I have ordered Crown Prince to execute Prince Nares,

60
00:06:18,603 --> 00:06:20,480
why did you neglect my order?

61
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:24,440
I didn't neglect your order.

62
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,270
I sent Mangjaparo

63
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:30,120
to escort Prince Nares here for investigation.

64
00:06:31,874 --> 00:06:35,080
Instead, he ambushed the prince and aiming for the life.

65
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:39,920
This is the reason why Prince Nares ran away.

66
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,480
Mangjaparo knew it well that you wouldn't have a heart to finish your task.

67
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:48,321
He deserved his penalty

68
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,040
falsely claim the Crown Prince's name.

69
00:06:51,943 --> 00:06:54,080
But he did nothing wrong for

70
00:06:54,377 --> 00:06:55,720
trying to execute the runaway rebel.

71
00:06:58,857 --> 00:06:59,840
Deputy Grand Minister,

72
00:07:01,203 --> 00:07:04,700
Mangjaparo's penalties shall be revoked. He can come back to work.

73
00:07:05,183 --> 00:07:06,680
As you command, Your Majesty.

74
00:07:06,837 --> 00:07:09,160
As for Crown Prince Mingyi Swa,

75
00:07:09,697 --> 00:07:13,600
I order you to lead the grand army, consisting of 500 elephants, 5,000 horses

76
00:07:14,223 --> 00:07:17,810
and 70,000 members of infantry to join Phraya Chanto's troop.

77
00:07:18,443 --> 00:07:21,360
You need to arrest Prince Nares for execution.

78
00:07:22,970 --> 00:07:25,200
This is your reparation.

79
00:07:42,397 --> 00:07:46,560
In wars, there are two sides; the victor and the loser.

80
00:07:51,683 --> 00:07:55,550
Thado Minsaw committed rebellion action but he refused to be punished.

81
00:07:55,937 --> 00:07:58,080
Instead, he ran away and died in the different city.

82
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,320
For his wife's sake,

83
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,640
as she is your mother and my elder sister,

84
00:08:05,157 --> 00:08:07,720
the execution of seven generations will be pardoned.

85
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:12,600
But your title as the Crown Prince's Royal Consort will be revoked.

86
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:17,440
It is up to the victor

87
00:08:18,783 --> 00:08:20,720
to decide the fate of the loser.

88
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,480
From now on,

89
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:29,080
there is no relationship between you and the Crown Prince.

90
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,720
Princess Natshin Medaw of Inwa needs to leave her place

91
00:08:32,943 --> 00:08:35,320
and stay with her mother in the back of the palace.

92
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,720
She can never leave Hongsawadi for the rest of her life.

93
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:46,680
If we want to be free,

94
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:53,560
we can't lose to any battle, not even once.

95
00:10:57,603 --> 00:11:01,604
Why did our soldiers look like this?

96
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,221
[Phraya Chanto]

97
00:11:03,303 --> 00:11:06,240
King Nares led his army to attack us early morning.

98
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:26,041
We can't fight against them so we need to withdraw and escape here, Your Highness.

99
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,880
More than half of our people are injured.

100
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:41,240
The rest were so exhausted.

101
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:46,440
These soldiers have followed me since the battle with Inwa,

102
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,881
the King ordered us to march

103
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:52,680
we didn’t get a proper rest because we needed to catch up with Prince Nares.

104
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:01,920
To fight in the battle, our physical health and mental health need to be strong.

105
00:12:03,450 --> 00:12:04,960
If we are not ready,

106
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,280
how can we fight the battle?

107
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,240
We are simply marching to the battle and waiting for them to kill us.

108
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,001
What's wrong?

109
00:12:16,357 --> 00:12:18,297
Help!

110
00:12:18,517 --> 00:12:19,720
Kid, are you alright?

111
00:12:19,937 --> 00:12:21,600
- Help!
- Are you okay, kid?

112
00:12:22,597 --> 00:12:23,960
Kid!

113
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,520
He's burning up. Do you have some medicine?

114
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,440
Get the medicine at the doctor's yurt.

115
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:32,960
Kid!

116
00:12:33,717 --> 00:12:35,240
Kid!

117
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,410
Kid!

118
00:12:41,730 --> 00:12:43,357
Kid!

119
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:19,520
How can we fight Prince Narest

120
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,087
when our soldiers look like this?

121
00:13:30,637 --> 00:13:34,600
My grand army just came back from Inwa battle as well.

122
00:13:37,643 --> 00:13:39,040
Some of them were injured while some were disabled.

123
00:13:41,870 --> 00:13:43,440
We're not better than yours.

124
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:50,800
It's the King's order. If we can't arrest Prince Nares,

125
00:13:51,097 --> 00:13:52,156
we can't return.

126
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,200
What other choices do we have, Your Highness?

127
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,200
[Battle Field in Lum Phli.]

128
00:15:18,657 --> 00:15:19,480
What are you trying to do, Brother?

129
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,360
Do you remember our lesson in sword?

130
00:15:34,317 --> 00:15:36,920
You like sword fighting, you practiced it for so long.

131
00:15:37,703 --> 00:15:38,880
But you didn't like it.

132
00:15:39,263 --> 00:15:41,290
You didn't like to practice it, you wanted the lesson to be over soon.

133
00:15:41,603 --> 00:15:44,160
I'm exhausted, let's do something else.

134
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,120
But it's not the time to break yet.

135
00:15:47,137 --> 00:15:49,720
When I wanted to stop practicing, I'd tell you like this.

136
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,440
Prince Nares won this round.

137
00:16:49,817 --> 00:16:51,480
Withdraw!

138
00:16:55,523 --> 00:16:56,524
Withdraw!

139
00:17:25,390 --> 00:17:28,880
You think that I love you so you can do whatever you please, Mingyi Swa?

140
00:17:51,010 --> 00:17:54,160
You need to say in here for a day, and think about your action,

141
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:57,440
what was the wrong thing you to me and to Hongsawadi?

142
00:18:42,743 --> 00:18:43,744
My aunt.

143
00:19:02,083 --> 00:19:05,400
I heard that you haven't eaten anything since yesterday.

144
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:10,480
I brought you some sugarcane juice to refresh you.

145
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,050
This is jail.

146
00:19:17,817 --> 00:19:20,160
It is not a place that you should visit.

147
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:28,120
Wherever you are

148
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,360
I will be there.

149
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,440
Please have a sip.

150
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,520
And you don't have to say anything.

151
00:20:05,277 --> 00:20:06,880
Don't ever come here again, please.

152
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,520
If my father finds out,

153
00:20:15,597 --> 00:20:17,240
he will be mad at you.

154
00:20:20,443 --> 00:20:24,680
The King ordered me to visit you here.

155
00:20:29,923 --> 00:20:33,880
King Nanda Bayin loves you with all of his heart.

156
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,080
You are put in jail

157
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,840
but he is the one who is more sorrowful.

158
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,680
I told my troops to retreat,

159
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,720
but it wasn't because I was afraid.

160
00:20:51,450 --> 00:20:55,000
I just wanted to save my soldiers.

161
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:01,200
In the future, if the others defy my command, not you,

162
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:02,920
what would you want me to do?

163
00:21:12,297 --> 00:21:13,440
Your Highness,

164
00:21:16,863 --> 00:21:21,160
he didn't mean to defy the royal decree,

165
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,680
instead he cared about his soldiers.

166
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,480
That's why he decided to do that.

167
00:21:29,183 --> 00:21:31,440
During wartime, we lost our soldiers along the way.

168
00:21:32,017 --> 00:21:35,520
If we aimed for something big, we needed to lose something behind.

169
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:37,880
If we failed to do so, we'd lose it all.

170
00:21:43,923 --> 00:21:46,040
If you cared about your soldiers like you said,

171
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:50,640
then you needed to tell them to march forward during battles.

172
00:21:51,083 --> 00:21:52,520
They would still have a chance to make it out alive.

173
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,920
If they decide to retreat per your command,

174
00:21:55,383 --> 00:21:57,760
they will come back to face death penalty according to the martial law.

175
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,601
Father?

176
00:22:02,601 --> 00:22:06,480
The soldiers who retreated deserved death penalty.

177
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,680
For your sake,

178
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:13,000
I only ordered them to be flogged with leather wire

179
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,360
and cut off their ears

180
00:22:15,930 --> 00:22:17,240
because they didn't listen to my command.

181
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:37,963
A sovereign's order is meant to follow.

182
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,240
Keep that in mind

183
00:22:43,663 --> 00:22:45,040
next time you decide to do something.

184
00:23:14,877 --> 00:23:15,878
Mingyi Swa.

185
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:47,720
[Sanphet Prasat Throne Hall, Ayutthaya]

186
00:24:06,737 --> 00:24:07,738
Brother.

187
00:24:11,017 --> 00:24:12,018
Khao!

188
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:31,480
You kept on marching back to the city without any rest, aren't you exhausted?

189
00:24:36,063 --> 00:24:37,760
Well, look at you.

190
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,800
You even get tanner and thinner.

191
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:44,880
Come on, he ate and slept in the battlefield.

192
00:24:45,157 --> 00:24:47,080
How good-looking do you expect him to be?

193
00:24:48,463 --> 00:24:51,120
I can't talk about my son's appearance at all?

194
00:24:54,420 --> 00:24:56,250
Please don't mention anything about getting tan.

195
00:24:56,517 --> 00:24:58,920
I'm still tan even I'm not in the battle.

196
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:02,960
Khao is the good-looking one.

197
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,360
He's too good-looking. Whenever he goes outside,

198
00:25:07,547 --> 00:25:11,250
court ladies keep on looking at him, they forget to do their work.

199
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,280
This is the only thing that I'm better than you.

200
00:25:15,483 --> 00:25:16,484
Come on!

201
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,400
Where is Princess Suphankalaya's procession reaching now?

202
00:25:22,783 --> 00:25:24,440
When will they arrive in the city?

203
00:25:26,870 --> 00:25:27,871
Well….

204
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:43,200
she's not coming back.

205
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:48,960
What? What is going on?

206
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:08,921
She left you the message.

207
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:15,760
She said that you would understand her once you read it.

208
00:26:36,437 --> 00:26:39,920
I, Suphankalaya

209
00:26:41,177 --> 00:26:44,800
humbly pay homage before the feet of Mother and Father

210
00:26:45,178 --> 00:26:48,440
with all of my heart.

211
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:55,400
I can't bring Min A Htwe back to Ayutthaya with me

212
00:26:56,137 --> 00:26:59,320
and I can't leave her here by herself.

213
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:03,760
That's why I can't go back with Nares to serve both of you

214
00:27:03,977 --> 00:27:05,440
like I've always wished to.

215
00:27:07,083 --> 00:27:09,640
I'm staying in Hongsawadi

216
00:27:10,410 --> 00:27:12,880
but my heart is loyal to both of you

217
00:27:13,730 --> 00:27:16,120
and Ayutthaya.

218
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:19,400
My loyalty won't fade away.

219
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:27,600
How can a mother

220
00:27:32,143 --> 00:27:33,920
leave her child behind?

221
00:27:42,630 --> 00:27:43,631
Father?

222
00:27:54,050 --> 00:27:55,840
We did so wrong to our daughter.

223
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:02,880
We left her there alone and she is surrounded with enemies.

224
00:28:05,130 --> 00:28:08,040
Ayutthaya and Hongsawadi will inevitably go to war.

225
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,440
Suphankalaya is living at the other side of the land.

226
00:28:18,250 --> 00:28:20,840
How can she survive those vultures?

227
00:28:29,350 --> 00:28:30,351
Oh, you're here.

228
00:28:34,890 --> 00:28:36,760
Where is your brother?

229
00:28:37,583 --> 00:28:39,280
He is still feeling unwell?

230
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,640
His body is getting better

231
00:28:43,321 --> 00:28:45,270
but his heart isn't getting any better.

232
00:28:49,123 --> 00:28:50,924
What? Who's there?

233
00:28:54,063 --> 00:28:56,320
You need to invite the Crown Prince here at this moment.

234
00:28:56,837 --> 00:28:59,040
I need to talk to him about war.

235
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:01,560
By your command, Your Majesty.

236
00:29:02,477 --> 00:29:04,400
My brother doesn't care about going to war.

237
00:29:05,690 --> 00:29:08,440
To make it worse, he favors the enemy.

238
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:12,960
The Crown Prince of Hongsawadi becomes like this,

239
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,040
when will our battle with Ayutthaya gain victory?

240
00:29:16,270 --> 00:29:17,480
I don't see it coming.

241
00:30:00,090 --> 00:30:01,560
Why are you sulking here?

242
00:30:03,057 --> 00:30:04,970
I told you to come and see me but you refused.

243
00:30:05,610 --> 00:30:07,280
Did you forget who you are?

244
00:30:11,670 --> 00:30:14,000
If you think that I don't deserve it,

245
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:18,680
then you can revoke my position.

246
00:30:19,763 --> 00:30:24,000
The Crown Prince is someone who will succeed my position to rule the land.

247
00:30:25,163 --> 00:30:26,700
You won't yearn for it at all?

248
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,161
I...

249
00:30:38,523 --> 00:30:40,400
can't be like you.

250
00:30:43,970 --> 00:30:45,037
What's wrong with being me?

251
00:30:46,463 --> 00:30:48,840
Am I too cruel to be a human?

252
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:54,440
Lan Xang, Yuan, Chiang Mai and Ayutthaya

253
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:56,100
they want to be the greatest of all.

254
00:30:58,100 --> 00:31:01,280
The strongest one is the victor.

255
00:31:02,110 --> 00:31:03,600
This is how the wars work.

256
00:31:04,077 --> 00:31:07,080
If you don't kill them first, then they will kill you.

257
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:10,877
You keep on killing one another

258
00:31:11,757 --> 00:31:13,600
only commoners are dead

259
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,280
not the rulers.

260
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:18,000
Everyone was born with duties.

261
00:31:18,761 --> 00:31:19,977
You know it well

262
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:24,640
how much blood and flesh was traded to build up the Kingdom of Pagan.

263
00:31:25,077 --> 00:31:26,520
Those people shouldn't be dead for nothing.

264
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:35,400
You need to focus on keeping this land for your kin,

265
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,561
Mingyi Swa.

266
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:26,031
I'd like to announce that Princess Yaza Datu Kalaya

267
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:30,640
will be the noble consort of Crown Prince Mingyi Swa.

268
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:33,440
I want to bless both of you

269
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:36,560
a lifetime of happiness relationship.

270
00:32:39,050 --> 00:32:41,080
- Your royal grace is boundless, Your Majesty.
- Your royal grace is boundless, Your Majesty.

271
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:55,480
After the royal wedding, the Crown Prince

272
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,280
needs to recruit his soliders and

273
00:32:59,497 --> 00:33:00,920
prepare his army

274
00:33:03,290 --> 00:33:05,400
to march and fight against Ayutthaya.

275
00:33:52,997 --> 00:33:55,040
May the triple gems of Buddhist

276
00:33:55,523 --> 00:33:57,637
and all angels

277
00:33:58,023 --> 00:34:00,680
to guard Ayutthaya.

278
00:34:02,263 --> 00:34:04,120
Please protect the city to be safe

279
00:34:05,463 --> 00:34:07,840
from generation to generation.

280
00:34:12,443 --> 00:34:15,240
Also, please protect Princess Suphankalaya.

281
00:34:17,503 --> 00:34:18,800
I wish for her to stay safe

282
00:34:20,317 --> 00:34:23,000
from all dangers, please.

283
00:34:54,663 --> 00:34:55,664
Father!

284
00:35:00,637 --> 00:35:01,638
Father!

285
00:35:05,457 --> 00:35:07,040
I'm doing fine.

286
00:35:14,097 --> 00:35:17,200
I went to pray last night and I fainted.

287
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,200
No, you're not fine.

288
00:35:21,317 --> 00:35:23,880
The doctor said that it's because of your blood pressure.

289
00:35:24,783 --> 00:35:27,520
If you are not getting better, you will go down with debility.

290
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:29,041
And it will affect your heart.

291
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:31,240
I am not dying.

292
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:36,680
Dam and Khao, come here.

293
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:49,480
Any reports on your tasks?

294
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:55,520
I ordered people living in the north, including Phitsanulok,

295
00:35:55,930 --> 00:35:58,920
Pichai, Sawankhalok, Sukhothai,

296
00:35:59,277 --> 00:36:01,000
Kamphaengphet and Phichit,

297
00:36:01,903 --> 00:36:03,320
to sell their rice, pack up and leave.

298
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:06,560
People from the outside needs to evacuate to the city already.

299
00:36:08,097 --> 00:36:09,098
Good.

300
00:36:09,730 --> 00:36:12,960
We can't let them stay there, when Hongsawadi army marches here,

301
00:36:13,363 --> 00:36:14,600
they would take our people.

302
00:36:16,190 --> 00:36:19,600
Khao, what about the wall reconstruction?

303
00:36:20,577 --> 00:36:22,600
You need to dig up moat from the east.

304
00:36:23,417 --> 00:36:26,960
Make sure that it is deep enough to be a river to circle around the city.

305
00:36:27,883 --> 00:36:29,280
Is it done?

306
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,360
We're working on it fast, Your Highness.

307
00:36:34,423 --> 00:36:35,600
Your Highness,

308
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:40,600
you should leave the children to take care of war preparation.

309
00:36:42,050 --> 00:36:43,880
If you're worried about it too much,

310
00:36:44,463 --> 00:36:46,281
your body will only get worse.

311
00:36:49,737 --> 00:36:52,120
King Nanda Bayin won't leave Ayutthaya at peace for sure.

312
00:36:53,890 --> 00:36:56,160
They will circle around and attack us until they get to us.

313
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,961
We will face with big war.

314
00:37:02,223 --> 00:37:04,560
Dam is brave

315
00:37:05,224 --> 00:37:08,120
but he is short-tempered, and only attacking.

316
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:12,240
Khao is more calm

317
00:37:13,937 --> 00:37:15,680
and he can watch his brother's back.

318
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:17,561
Both of you

319
00:37:19,690 --> 00:37:21,562
need to stay together.

320
00:37:22,990 --> 00:37:23,991
Remember that.

321
00:37:29,237 --> 00:37:30,238
Yes, Your Highness.

322
00:38:55,350 --> 00:38:56,520
Mingyi Swa

323
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:59,041
led the troops to attack Ayutthaya

324
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:02,920
according to his father's command.

325
00:39:04,903 --> 00:39:06,120
But he lost the battle

326
00:39:07,237 --> 00:39:09,280
for three times already.

327
00:39:36,750 --> 00:39:40,680
On Sunday, 9th lunar day in 12th month

328
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:43,880
Chula Sakarat, Minor Era Year 948.

329
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:49,160
King Nanda Bayin led 250,000 soldiers

330
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:53,200
along with elephants and horses to march to Ayutthaya

331
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:55,600
by himself.

332
00:39:58,403 --> 00:40:00,480
Suphankalaya sent a message that

333
00:40:01,257 --> 00:40:04,200
King Nanda Bayin is leading the grand army by himself,

334
00:40:04,903 --> 00:40:09,120
including 250,000 soliders, 1,200 elephants and 12,000 horses.

335
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:11,400
The troops from other cities will joing them,

336
00:40:12,097 --> 00:40:13,560
up to 24 troops.

337
00:40:16,017 --> 00:40:18,960
Oh Lord! 24 troops?

338
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:21,800
You're scared, Phet?

339
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:27,860
Of course not, the worst case is that I'm dead.

340
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:33,400
Sri and Phet,

341
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:35,760
you need to flock villagers from the outside

342
00:40:36,150 --> 00:40:37,960
to stay behind the city's wall immediately.

343
00:40:39,257 --> 00:40:42,258
And you, Duang, you need to need the soliders to collect food

344
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:45,720
and villagers' produce to store behind the wall.

345
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,441
Yes, Your Highness.

346
00:40:51,777 --> 00:40:53,280
Burn down all houses

347
00:40:53,823 --> 00:40:55,560
don't let the enemies stay in any of them.

348
00:40:56,097 --> 00:40:57,640
Burn them down! Come on!

349
00:41:04,997 --> 00:41:05,998
Khao.

350
00:41:06,670 --> 00:41:10,560
We need to prepare the best army to honor and welcome King Nanda Bayin.

351
00:42:10,363 --> 00:42:11,600
I went to look around.

352
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,320
We are outnumbered, their soldiers are so much more than ours.

353
00:42:19,757 --> 00:42:22,200
Then we need to approach them directly.

354
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,800
We can't make this battle last longer.

355
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:28,080
We need to attack them when they are least expected.

356
00:42:28,377 --> 00:42:30,700
Kill most of them in the shortest of time.

357
00:42:30,837 --> 00:42:32,050
Then we will march back to the camp.

358
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:34,200
I will lead the troops.

359
00:42:35,280 --> 00:42:36,360
You can't!

360
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,560
One commander is worth more than thousands of soldiers.

361
00:42:40,903 --> 00:42:42,920
- You can't do that!
- Why is that?

362
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,880
If I am worth more than thousands of soldiers

363
00:42:46,117 --> 00:42:48,000
then they will get scared so fast just a glance of me.

364
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:53,600
Then I shall lead the troops.

365
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:58,240
You are the Crown Prince of Ayutthaya.

366
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:01,120
You can't risk your life like that.

367
00:43:03,697 --> 00:43:05,480
We are outnumbered and encouragement is important.

368
00:43:05,897 --> 00:43:08,880
If I stay behind, just to give orders, the soldiers won't dare to march forward.

369
00:43:10,280 --> 00:43:11,320
You all need to watch me!

370
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:14,280
Follow my lead and that is my command.

371
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:16,281
Yes, Your Highness.

372
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,480
I am my father's son

373
00:43:45,650 --> 00:43:48,000
and a Crown Prince of Hongsawadi.

374
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:51,480
I was born with this duty.

375
00:43:52,083 --> 00:43:55,400
I can't change that despite how much I dislike it.

376
00:43:57,077 --> 00:43:58,760
Duties are like smoke and cloud

377
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:00,520
they're hovering the sun.

378
00:44:01,723 --> 00:44:05,760
Our wishes can't come true.

379
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:10,440
From now on, we should perform our duties well.

380
00:44:12,050 --> 00:44:13,200
If we meet in the future,

381
00:44:14,090 --> 00:44:15,240
do not hold back.
